<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 2 Hezbollah Guerrillas Killed in S. Lebanon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, March 1 (Xinhua) -- Two guerrillas of the
Iranian-backed Hezbollah, or Party of God, were killed in south
Lebanon Sunday, Hezbollah sources said Monday.
</P>
<P>
They were killed during conflicts with Israeli forces in the
Israeli occupied border zone in south Lebanon, the sources said,
without elaborating.
</P>
<P>
Hezbollah is leading a guerrilla war in the country trying to
oust Israeli forces from south Lebanon where the Jewish state
set up a self-declared security zone in 1985 to allegedly protect
its north from Lebanese guerrillas' cross-border attacks.
</P>
<P>
The fresh fatalities raised to five the number of Hezbollah
guerrillas killed in south Lebanon since the start of this year.
</P>
<P>
Also on Sunday, Hezbollah detonated a twin roadside bomb
inside the border zone, killing four Israelis, including a
general and a journalist.
</P>
<P>
Brig. Gen Erez Gerstein, 38, the head of the Israeli military
liaison unit with the pro-Israeli South Lebanon Army, became the
most senior Israeli officer killed in Lebanon since the 1982
Israeli invasion.
</P>
<P>
Hezbollah's deadly attack provoked swift retaliation from
Israeli forces whose artillery and warplanes pounded the party's
bases throughout Lebanon. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
