<HEADLINE> Nigerian Elections Said "Peaceful and Well Organized" </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, March 1 (Xinhua) -- Leader of the Observer Group
of the Organization of African Unity (OAU) to the Nigerian
elections, ALi Hassan Mwinyi, said Monday that initial reports
reflect "generally peaceful and well organized polls", an OAU
press release issued here said.
</P>
<P>
The press release quoted the former Tanzanian President as
saying in a statement that "given Nigeria's recent history and the
urgent need to see the return to an elected civilian government,
these elections have surpassed all our expectations."
</P>
<P>
The OAU Observer Group to the elections in Nigeria had deployed
76 observers drawn from 18 African countries, the statement said,
adding that 32 OAU teams, operating in teams of 2 or 3, have
observed the presidential elections conducted on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The OAU Observer Group to the elections in Nigeria will be
issuing its full and complete statement on the conduct of the
presidential elections
soon, according to the statement. 
</P>
</TEXT>
