<HEADLINE> Three Killed in Swiss Helicopter Crash </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, March 1 (Xinhua) -- A helicopter of Air Glaciers
crashed in the area of Stalden in the southern Swiss canton of
Valais on Sunday, killing all the three passengers on board,
according to a Swiss news agency report on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The three men, the helicopter pilot, the head of the national
road service, and his assistant, were on a flight of inspection to
assess the danger of avalanches. The helicopter had obviously
flown into the cable of a private cableway, said a spokesman of
the cantonal police.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the report said that the danger of avalanches in the
Swiss Alps had begun to decrease, with many of the closed roads to
be re-opened soon. 
</P>
</TEXT>
