<HEADLINE> HK's Orange To Recruit Thousands In UK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, March 1 (Xinhua) -- Orange, the mobile phone company
largely owned by Hutchison Whampoa of Hongkong, is to recruit an
extra 2,000 staff in the UK over the next two years, the Invest in
Britain Bureau announced Monday.
</P>
<P>
Chief operating officer Bob Fuller said: "Our aim is to offer
the best quality, the best services and the best network" to cope
with rising demand for mobile phones.
</P>
<P>
"To deliver this we need to recruit and train the best people
so that we also provide the best customer service. Hence our plan
to create 2000 new jobs," Fuller added.
</P>
<P>
Orange made an operating profit of some 24.6 million U.S.
dollars in the year to December 31, 1998.
</P>
<P>
In December, the company announced the opening of a new
state-of-the-art call center at Peterlee in Norther East England
with a workforce of up to 500 people. 
</P>
</TEXT>
