inside the Israeli occupied border zone in south Lebanon, killing
Brig. Gen Erez Gerstein, the head of the Israeli army's liaison
unit with the pro-Israeli South Lebanon Army (SLA), and three
others.
</P>
<P>
This is the second heavy loss the Israeli forces suffered in
south Lebanon in less than a week. on Tuesday, Three Israeli
officers were killed and five others wounded in an ambush staged
by Hezbollah in eastern Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
In response, Israeli warplanes blasted Hezbollah's suspected
bases in the country's southern and eastern areas later Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Israel said the air strike on Hezbollah would continue for
a number of days.
</P>
<P>
Nasrallah warned that any large-scale aggression the Jewish
state dared to conduct would lead to its abortion.
</P>
<P>
The Iranian-backed guerrilla group is spearheading a war in
south Lebanon trying to oust Israeli forces and its ally SLA from
the country.
</P>
<P>
Israel set up a self-declared security zone in south Lebanon
in 1985 with the claimed aim of protecting its north from
Lebanese guerrillas' cross-border attacks. 
