opening of a municipal office and an educational complex on the
disputed island of Abu Musa.
</P>
<P>
The UAE denounced the move as a breach of the memorandum of
understanding reached between the two countries, said Mohamed
Ahmed al-Mahmoud, UAE permanent delegate to the league.
</P>
<P>
He made the remarks after handing the complaint to Arab League
Secretary General Esmat Abdel-Meguid, Egypt's Middle East News
Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Iran has opened a municipal office on Abu Musa for its local
elections last Friday, the first since the 1979 Islamic revolution.
</P>
<P>
Iran started a nine-day military exercise Saturday in the
Persian Gulf and the Gulf of Oman, which includes the seas around
Abu Musa.
</P>
<P>
Both the UAE and Iran have claimed sovereignty over the three
islands of Abu Musa, Lesser and Greater Tunbs near the mouth of the
strategic Gulf.
</P>
<P>
A-Mahmoud said the UAE considered all the previous and future
practices by Iran on Abu Musa as "provocative and unwarranted."
</P>
<P>
Iran and the UAE have expressed readiness to resolve the
dispute by peaceful means. But the UAE favors a solution through
international arbitration while Iran insists on bilateral
negotiations. 
</P>
