<HEADLINE> Lantern Festival Celebrated in Hong Kong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, March 2 (Xinhua) -- A great number of Hong Kong
families walked out of their homes Tuesday evening to enjoy
themselves under the full moon on the Chinese Lantern Festival,
the 15th day in the first month on the traditional Chinese lunar
calendar.
</P>
<P>
A celebration held Tuesday evening at Ko Shan Road Park in
Kowloon attracted thousands of visitors.
</P>
<P>
A special collection of festive puppets named "Rabbits Greeting
the Advent of Spring" was presented at the celebration by the
Guangdong Province Puppet Troupe to herald the Year of the Rabbit.
</P>
<P>
In addition, a wide variety of colorful lanterns were displayed
at the gala organized by the Provisional Urban Council. A huge
lantern called "the dragon and the phoenix chasing the moon" was
also displayed.
</P>
<P>
Other programs included a Chinese orchestral concert, a shadow
puppet show, a magic show, roving street acts, traditional arts
and crafts stalls, lantern-riddle games, Chinese chess games and
games stalls.
</P>
<P>
A series of performances with strong Chinese traditional and
ethnic characteristics such as the Chinese Opera, folk songs and
dance were also staged at Ko Shan Theater.
</P>
<P>
In the evening, a lantern carnival was organized by the
Provisional Regional Council (Pro RC) at the Kwai Chung Sports
Ground.
</P>
<P>
This year the Pro RC organized two lantern carnivals to
celebrate the Chinese Lantern Festival in the "New Territories."
</P>
<P>
The one held Sunday night at the Tai Po Playground attracted
some 30,000 visitors.
</P>
<P>
The programs included traditional variety street shows with
performers in costumes; folk games such as lantern riddles, crafts
demonstration and fortune telling, Chinese operatic performances;
and a pop concert.
</P>
<P>
Large-scale lanterns in traditional settings, which are
indispensable on the occasion, were set at the venue.
</P>
<P>
One of the highlights was the broadcast or bird chirping in the
classic Chinese lantern setting featuring 100 birds paying tribute
to a five-meter-high phoenix.
</P>
<P>
Celebration was also held on the Hong Kong Island. The Wan Chai
Culture, Recreational and Sports Association organized a carnival
on Sunday to celebrate the Lantern Festival in Southorn Playground.
</P>
<P>
The carnival featured lion dances, game stalls, palm reading,
children's choir, singing and lucky draw.
</P>
<P>
Traditionally, the full moon on the night of the Lantern
Festival indicates family reunion for the Chinese people. The
Lantern Festival is also called the Chinese Valentine's Day in
Hong Kong as the full moon forecasts a happy marriage. 
</P>
</TEXT>
