</P>
<P>
-- U.S. intelligence services infiltrated agents and espionage
equipment for three years into United Nations arms control teams
in Iraq to eavesdrop on the Iraq military without the knowledge of
the U.N. agency that it used to disguise its work, according to U.
S. government employees and documents describing the classified
operation.
</P>
