criticized the International Olympic Committee for a lack of
openness and ethical control and accused the organization of
tolerating a culture of gift-giving that is "potentially illegal
and inevitably corrupt" in the third major report on the Salt Lake
City Olympic scandal.
</P>
<P>
The New York Times:
</P>
<P>
-- A United Nations panel has recommended that about a dozen
senior Khmer Rouge officials be tried by a new international
tribunal for crimes against humanity while they ruled Cambodia,
diplomats and senior administration officials said.
</P>
<P>
The Wall Street Journal:
</P>
<P>
-- The U.S. Postal Service, moving to bolster its international
mail operations and take on newly aggressive overseas post offices,
is forming an alliance with DHL Worldwide Express Inc. to jointly
offer a two-day-delivery service between certain U.S. cities and
Europe. 
