<HEADLINE> Life of Flood Victims in Hubei Well Taken Care Of </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 2 (Xinhua) -- Victims of last summer's severe
flooding in central Hubei Province have all fairly well resettled
thanks in part to efforts by central and local governments.
</P>
<P>
Jiang Zhuping, Hubei provincial governor who heads the province'
s delegation of deputies to the National People's Congress to
attend the congress' annual session here, said that most of the
290,000 families displaced by flooding last summer had moved into
new houses before the Chinese lunar new year in mid-February.
</P>
<P>
The provincial government provided a relief fund of 17 million
yuan (about US$2 million) prior to the traditional Chinese
festival to ensure that the most needy have ample food for the
holidays.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, it had distributed 23 million yuan to flood victims to
help them tide over the winter.
</P>
<P>
Relief funds and donations totaling more than 1.2 billion yuan
in value have been provided so far to flood victims in the
province, according to the provincial governor.
</P>
<P>
Other problems concerning people's life like access to medical
care and school education have been properly resolved, Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
Local farmers are now busy working at water conservancy and
flood prevention projects, with some of them having been completed.
</P>
</TEXT>
