<HEADLINE> CPPCC Members Cherish Memory of Famous Woman Writer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 2 (Xinhua) -- Members of the National Committee
of the Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC)
who are here to attend the upcoming Second Session of the Ninth
CPPCC National Committee have expressed their profound grief over
the death of their counterpart Xie Bingxin.
</P>
<P>
Xie, one of the most prominent writers in China, died Sunday at
the age of 99. She was Honorary Chairperson of the China
Association for Promoting Democracy.
</P>
<P>
CPPCC National Committee members from China's art circle agree
that the death of the woman writer is a great loss to the country.
"The power of her works comes from the people," said Yuan Shihai,
a well-known Peking Opera master from the Chinese Capital.
</P>
<P>
Most of Xie's works are written for young people. In the 1980s
and 1990s, she raised many proposals on behalf of teachers,
calling for greater attention to be paid to the development of the
country's education, according to the members.
</P>
<P>
So far, departments concerned and Xie's relatives have received
many letters of condolences from home and abroad. 
</P>
</TEXT>
