<HEADLINE> Russia Urges End to Bombing in Iraq </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, March 2 (Xinhua) -- Russia on Tuesday called for an end
to the bombings being conducted by the United States and Britain
in the no-fly zones in Iraq.
</P>
<P>
"We get the impression that an attempt is being made to get the
international community used to the actions which run counter to
the basic norms and principles of international law," Foreign
Ministry Spokesman Vladimir Rakhmanin told a briefing.
</P>
<P>
The bombings "cannot be justified from either a legal or moral
point of view and hinder the settlement of the Iraqi problem,
which is being pursued in the U.N. Security Council," Rakhmanin
said.
</P>
<P>
"We stated repeatedly that the no-fly zones were set up without
authorization of the U.N. Security Council. They are illegitimate
from the point of view of U.N. rules and international laws," the
spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
"Remarks that such zones are necessary to protect the civil
population from repression are beyond criticism," Rakhmanin said.
</P>
<P>
"Facts prove just the opposite. The list of civilian victims
who have suffered from the military actions being carried out by
the U.S. and British air forces is growing," he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
