<HEADLINE> Vietnamese Party Leader Says Visit to China Successful </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, March 2 (Xinhua) -- General Secretary Le Kha Phieu of
the Vietnamese Communist Party on Tuesday called his six-day China
tour a success and said Sino-Vietnamese relations are set to
develop in the future.
</P>
<P>
Le arrived in Hanoi Tuesday afternoon after he wound up his
official goodwill visit to China.
</P>
<P>
He described his talks with Chinese leaders as "quite frank and
cordial" and pledged that Vietnam will firmly adhere to socialism
with Vietnamese characteristics.
</P>
<P>
He expressed belief that the Sino-Vietnamese relationship will
develop in a proper manner and asked people and authorities at all
levels to do their utmost to encourage the bilateral relationship.
</P>
<P>
Vice Premier and Foreign Minister Nguyen Manh Cam, who
accompanied Le on the visit to China, said three prominent
achievements made during the visit have boosted the relationship
to a new high.
</P>
<P>
The two nations agreed to build long-term, stable, good
neighborly and all-round cooperative relations on the basis of the
acknowledged principles of the joint statements after the
normalization of Sino-Vietnamese ties and the consensus reached by
their Party and state leaders.
</P>
<P>
The second achievement was that China and Vietnam agreed to
sign an accord on the land border in 1999 and to settle the issue
of border demarcation in Beibu Wan (Vinh Bac Bo) in 2000.
</P>
<P>
The third achievement, said Nguyen, was that the two sides
strengthened mutual understanding through talks and meetings.
</P>
