<HEADLINE> People's Daily Editorial Hails Opening of CPPCC Session </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 2 (Xinhua) -- The Wednesday issue of the People'
s Daily, China's leading newspaper, will carry an editorial
marking the opening tomorrow afternoon of the Second Session of
the Ninth National Committee of the Chinese People's Political
Consultative Conference (CPPCC), the country's top advisory body.
</P>
<P>
The editorial, titled "Discussing matters of vital importance
in solidarity and promoting development through maintaining
stability," says that the CPPCC, an organization representing the
widest united patriotic front in China, is an important body for
the multi-party cooperation and political consultation under the
leadership of the Communist Party of China (CPC), as well as a
vital component of China's socialist political system.
</P>
<P>
"It is conducive to developing socialist democracy, to
increasing unity among people from all ethnic groups and various
sectors, to bringing the superiority of the socialist system into
full play, and to mobilizing all positive factors for building
socialism with Chinese characteristics under the CPC leadership,"
the article adds.
</P>
<P>
Describing 1998 as an "extremely unusual year," the editorial
says that the past year has witnessed that the Chinese people,
under the strong leadership of the CPC Central Committee with
Jiang Zemin at the core, have withstood the Asian financial crisis,
have overcome a devastating flooding and have achieved new
progress in reform, opening-up and the socialist modernization
drive, which have drawn worldwide attention.
</P>
<P>
"All these achievements are closely related to the painstaking
efforts of the CPPCC National Committee and CPPCC organizations at
all levels across the country," it says.
</P>
<P>
The editorial goes on to say that in the year of 1999, the
Chinese people will celebrate the 50th founding anniversary of the
People's Republic of China, as well as the return of Macao to its
motherland by the end of the year.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, it says, it remains an extremely arduous task to
continue reforms, speed up growth and maintain stability in the
new year.
</P>
<P>
"This new situation has posed a greater challenge to the work
of the CPPCC while providing more room for the functioning of the
CPPCC," it says.
</P>
<P>
It expresses the belief that the CPPCC will continue with its
efforts to promote unity and democracy in China, actively perform
its duty of political consultation, democratic supervision and
participation in various government affairs, and unite all forces
that can be united with.
</P>
<P>
"We also believe that with the joint efforts of all CPPCC
National Committee members, the upcoming session will surely turn
out to be a democratic, truth-seeking, united and inspiring
meeting," it concludes. 
</P>
</TEXT>
