October 31 in Kunming, capital of southwest China's Yunnan
Province, will be the last worldwide horticulture fair held this
century.
</P>
<P>
Yunnan has invested over a billion yuan to create gardens for
the exposition, and now 95 percent of the projects have been
completed with more than 300,000 trees and 300,000 square meters
of lawn planted.
