<HEADLINE> China to Extend More Loans to Rural Areas </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 2 (Xinhua) -- The People's Bank of China (PBOC),
the country's central bank, announced today that China will extend
more loans to its rural areas in an effort to increase farmers'
income.
</P>
<P>
The PBOC urged rural financial institutions to readjust their
credit structure and improve the quality of their loans as well as
extend their loans to the rural market.
</P>
<P>
Rural financial institutions are also instructed to improve
their financial services, begin offering credit, extend housing
loans to farmers, and make loans for education.
</P>
<P>
Priority, however, will be given to loans for agricultural and
rural businesses. As local financial institutions endeavor to
extend more loans, they may be able to receive support from the
PBOC branches in cases of fund shortages.
</P>
<P>
The PBOC also urged rural financial institutions to increase
the quality of their loans and reduce non-performing loans to
prevent financial risks. The central bank also requires local
governments to establish guarantee funds to help farmers obtain
loans for expanded production.
</P>
<P>
In addition, rural financial institutions are to support the
processing of farm produce, and fuel the industrialization of
agriculture, according to the PBOC.
</P>
<P>
The central bank will commit itself to supervising financial
institutions in order to help them improve their financial
services and reduce non-performing loans. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
