<HEADLINE> Beijing Begins Daily Air-Quality Report </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 2 (Xinhua) -- Beijing today began issuing daily
rather than weekly air-quality reports to demonstrate the city's
resolve in solving its pollution problem.
</P>
<P>
Today's report by the Municipal Environmental Protection
Monitor Center was published in major local newspapers, and said
the city was suffering third-degree air pollution (the worst is
five degrees) and the biggest pollutant is nitrogen oxide.
</P>
<P>
Environmentalists said that daily updates will be of great
value to local residents and will make the public more aware of
environmental protection.
</P>
<P>
Beijing began to release air-quality reports on February 28
last year, and they have proved effective in pressuring the
government to take corresponding efforts to deal with the city's
air pollution.
</P>
<P>
According to the reports for January, the density of noxious
pollutants in the air was reduced by over 10 percent compared with
the previous month. 
</P>
</TEXT>
