BEIJING, March 2 (Xinhua) -- China and Ghana, which will play
in the same group at the Women's World Cup this summer, will meet
next weekend in a friendly in Shunde, Guangdong Province, soccer
officials said on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
China will face the women's soccer powerhouse Sweden, the host
of the Sydney Olympic Games Australia and the African champions
Ghana in Group D in the World Cup for Women, which runs from June
19 to July 10 in the United States.
</P>
<P>
Ma Yuan'an, head coach of the women's Chinese team, greeted
this friendly as a good chance to get to know each other before
China formally take on the African team, which is the first time
to qualify for the tournament.
</P>
<P>
FIFA, the world soccer ruling body, has decided to use the
World Cup in part to determine qualifiers for the 2000 Sydney
Olympics soccer tournament.
</P>
<P>
FIFA ruled that if the eight quarter-finalists in the 16-team
World Cup include Australia, then all those eight teams will make
the Games, if not, the four semifinalists and the best three
losing quarter-finals get in. 
</P>
</TEXT>
