<HEADLINE> Sun Jun Seeded at All England Badminton </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, March 2 (Xinhua) -- Chinese shuttler Sun Jun has been
seeded 5/8 player at the All England Open Badminton Championships,
according to a press release from the organizers on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Sun Jun, the top singles player in China, defeated world number
one Peter Gade christensen of Denmark to win the Grand Prix in
Brunei last month.
</P>
<P>
Gade, who dominated the men's singles event last year, is
seeded first for the All England Championships, one of the most
prestigious tournaments in the world.
</P>
<P>
Fung Permadi of Chinese Taipei is second while Budi Santoso of
Indonesia and Poul-Erik Hoyer-Larsen of Denmark are seeded 3/4.
</P>
<P>
In the women's singles section, Dan Camila Martin will meet
challenge from her Chinese and Indonesia rivals.
</P>
<P>
Martin is seeded first and Chinese Zhou Mi second.
</P>
<P>
World champion Ye Zhaoying and her compatriot Dai Yun, who
finished runner-up to world number three Zhang Ning of China at
the Grand Prix, are 3/4 seeded for the tournament, which is slated
for March 9 to 14 in Birmingham.
