<HEADLINE> Another Bomb Found in Zambia's Capital </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
LUSAKA, March 2 (Xinhua) -- Another bomb has been found under
a Zambia Electricity Supply Corporation (ZESCO) pylon in Bauleni
area southeast of the capital Lusaka where nine others exploded on
Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Chief Government Spokesman, Newstead Zimba, said in a
statement released in Lusaka Tuesday that the bomb was discovered
Monday by ZESCO workers who were carrying out repairs to other
pylons which were damaged in an earlier attack.
</P>
<P>
He said the workers also found some explosives at the bomb
site where nine other bombs were planted and exploded.
</P>
<P>
Zimba said the new bomb brings to 15 the number of bombs found
in Lusaka.
</P>
<P>
Last Sunday, a series of bomb explosions occurred at the
Angolan embassy and four other scenes in Lusaka, one of the two
security guards at the Angolan embassy was killed while the other
was seriously injured. 
</P>
</TEXT>
