<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Macao Jobless Rate Rises </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, March 2 (Xinhua) -- Macao's unemployment rate from
November last year to January this year reached 5.6 percent,
statistics released Tuesday by the Macao Census and Statistics
Department show.
</P>
<P>
The figure was 0.2 percent higher than that during the October-
December period of 1998 and an increase of 2.8 percent over the
figure between November of 1997 and January 1998.
</P>
<P>
Affected by unfavorable economic conditions in its surrounding
areas, Macao has been suffering from economic difficulties over
the past years. Trade unions and other social bodies have urged
the government to create more jobs and cut the number of laborers
coming from elsewhere. 
</P>
</TEXT>
