<HEADLINE> Beijing, Tianjin Celebrate Lantern Festival </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 2 (Xinhua) -- People in Beijing and Tianjin held
many activities today to celebrate the traditional Lantern
Festival, which falls on the 15th of the first lunar month.
</P>
<P>
Colorful lamps were hung in front of the parks in Beijing, and
red lanterns festooned along Qianmen and Xidan streets lent the
downtown area a festive glow.
</P>
<P>
Many people gathered around a machine making sweet dumplings at
Xindong'an Market, where Mrs. Liu told Xinhua that she could be
sure the newly made sweet dumplings are fresh and delicious.
</P>
<P>
Chinese usually eat sweet dumplings made of glutinous rice
flour at family reunions on the day of the Lantern Festival, and
about five million kilograms of sweet dumplings will be sold in
Beijing's markets this year.
</P>
<P>
The Lantern Festival coincides with the eve of International
Women's Day. and the Beijing Municipal Women's Federation invited
many laid-off women to celebrate the festivals and conveyed
greetings to all laid-off women workers in the city.
</P>
<P>
Nearly 10,000 people in Tianjin went to the city's amusement
park to enjoy the red lanterns and the song and dance performances.
</P>
<P>
People in the rural areas around Tianjin were busy setting off
firecrackers, and drum and dance teams made up of more than 2,000
middle-school students gave brilliant performances in Jinghai
County.  
</P>
</TEXT>
