journalists had registered at the center, including 292 from Hong
Kong, Macao and Taiwan and 342 from more than 130 foreign news
organizations.
</P>
<P>
The NPC session is scheduled to open on March 5 and the CPPCC
national committee session tomorrow afternoon.
</P>
<P>
"We will try our best to provide convenience to your work,"
Shen told reporters, adding that the press center has prepared
namelists of all NPC deputies and CPPCC members and about 20 kinds
of handouts about China's newly enacted laws and vital economic
and social development data.
</P>
<P>
For the first time, the center has opened IDD phone service and
even a cafe for reporters, according to Shen. 
