<HEADLINE> Annual CPPCC Session Ready to Open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 2 (Xinhua) -- All preparations for the upcoming
Second Session of the Ninth National Committee of the Chinese
People's Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC) have been
completed, announced a spokesman for the annual gathering, which
is to be convened from March 3-11.
</P>
<P>
Spokesman Tian Zengpei briefed a group of local and overseas
journalists here today at the first news conference of the annual
CPPCC National Committee session.
</P>
<P>
Over the past year, members of the CPPCC have played an active
role in political consultations and democratic supervision and
participated in political and government affairs by making
investigations into a wide range of major issues attracting
popular concern, Tian said.
</P>
<P>
The major issues include the handling of layoffs from state-
owned enterprises, implementation of the state policy of
reinvigorating the nation through science/technology and education,
agriculture and rural work, control of major rivers and lakes, and
the economic situation, according to the spokesman.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman answered questions raised by reporters concerning
responsibilities of CPPCC members, China's reunification, public
security and efforts to ensure the quality of civil engineering
projects.
</P>
<P>
He said that a special news section for the CPPCC session will
be opened at the news center and that reporters will be allowed to
attend some panel discussions as well as two news briefings on the
country's efforts to stimulate domestic demand and protect the
environment.
</P>
<P>
Local journalists will be invited to attend a group interview
with CPPCC National Committee members from Macao, Tian said. China
will resume the exercise of sovereignty over Macao on December 20
this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
