<HEADLINE> Japan's Jobless Rate at Record High for Third Straight Month </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, March 2 (Xinhua) -- Japan's unemployment rate stood at a
record high of 4.4 percent in January for the third straight month,
the Management and Coordination Agency said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The number of unemployed climbed to 340,000 from a year earlier
to one million due to corporate restructuring, bankruptcy and
other reasons, according to the agency.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the number of jobholders also declined for the 12th
consecutive month to 63.8 million, down 750,000, the highest
figure since August 1975 when 870,000 were recorded.
</P>
<P>
In a separate report, the Labor Ministry said the seasonally
adjusted figures showed a ratio of 49 vacancies for every 100 job
seekers in January. 
</P>
</TEXT>
