<HEADLINE> New Methods Needed to Stimulate Consumer Consumption </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 2 (Xinhua) -- Chen Bangzhu, director of the
State Economic and Trade Commission, has stressed that there are
new opportunities to stimulate domestic consumption this year,
according to today's China Youth Daily.
</P>
<P>
Chen made the remark at a national conference on commodity
circulation. He said that the purchase of houses and related
commodities, vehicles, information industry products and tourism
products will certainly indicate an increase in domestic demand.
</P>
<P>
He noted that the above-mentioned sectors did not become hot
spots in the economy last year mainly because of lack of consumer-
oriented policies.
</P>
<P>
Chen said that the new policies focus on the expansion of
consumer credit, the establishment of laws governing rental sales
and the improvement of auction operations.
</P>
<P>
He added that car installments should be further encouraged
and installment payments for daily necessities and large farm
machines can be introduced in some areas in the country.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, more research work should be done on the sale of
stored goods and outdated goods in order to bring about more
effective means to stimulate consumption.  
</P>
