<HEADLINE> Major News Items in Leading French Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, March 2 (Xinhua) -- The following are major news items
in leading French newspapers on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Liberation:
</P>
<P>
-- The Israeli army have launched its most intensive attack
against the Hezbollah guerrillas since its punitive operation in
1996. In 24 hours, Israeli warplanes and helicopters conducted
about 20 raids against the enemy positions, while hundreds of
shells were fired, mainly on the valley of Bekaa in southeast
Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
-- Iranian President Mohammed Khatami won his first great
victory since his election in May 1997 in the municipal elections
last week. The provisionally figures provided by the Iranian
Interior Ministry said that nine partisans of Khatami has won the
presidency of municipal councils out of a total of 15 municipal
councils.
</P>
<P>
Le Figaro:
</P>
<P>
-- Experts attending a conference of the Organization for
Economic Cooperation and Development (OECD) on the employment of
youths held in Washington from Monday admitted that all the
predictions on the employment of youths have failed, as
unemployment among youths has only increased and economic
situation among people aged from 15 to 24 has deteriorated.
</P>
<P>
-- The neighboring countries of Colombia have reinforced troop
deployment along their borders because of frequent incursion by
guerrillas, para-military men and arms and drug traffickers from
Colombia. 
</P>
