<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bangkok Aims to Become World Gems, Jewelry Center </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, March 2 (Xinhua) -- Thailand is stepping up its
efforts to become the world's new gems and jewelry hub in the near
future, Thai Deputy Commerce Ministry Pravich Ratanapian said
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
To achieve the goal, he said, Thailand would hold two
international exhibitions and trade fairs on gems and jewelry this
year to promote the country's promising prospect as the world's
new production and trade center.
</P>
<P>
The two exhibitions, the 23rd and 24th of its kinds in Bangkok,
would be held on between March 10 and 13, and between September 29
and October 2 respectively.
</P>
<P>
The Commerce Ministry's Export Promotion Department would
sponsor the 23rd exhibition, while the 24th event would be solely
organized by the Thai Gems and Jewelry Traders' Association to
promote the private sector's role in the lucrative industry.
</P>
<P>
Gems and jewelry traders and firms from various countries are
expected to take part in the forthcoming events, which will not
only boost Thailand's business potential and reputation, but also
help local gems and jewelry producers and traders to improve
quality and designs of their products to meet the international
standard.
</P>
<P>
Thailand had also set a clear target to increase export of Thai
gems and jewelry by five percent this year to 60 billion baht (1.6
billion U.S. dollars) from 57.4 billion baht (1.5 billion dollars)
last year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
