<HEADLINE> hke030239-Myanmar Leader Calls for Rapid Agricultural Development </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, March 2 (Xinhua) -- Myanmar leader Senior-General Than
Shwe Tuesday called on peasants in the country to make efforts for
rapid agricultural development and flourishing agro-based
industries and other industries for overall development of the
national economy.
</P>
<P>
In his message on the occasion of the 1999 Myanmar Peasants Day
which falls on Tuesday, Than Shwe, chairman of the State Peace and
Development Council, stressed the need to concentrate on
agricultural development in all ways to extend cultivation of
crops for self-sufficiency of yearly increasing population.
</P>
<P>
He urged the farmers to take it as a national duty to strive
for cultivation of a total of 18 million acres (7.29 million
hectares) of monsoon and summer paddy and get an average per-acre
(0.405 hectare) yield of 100 baskets (2.09 tons) every year for
sufficiency and surplus of paddy, the staple crop of Myanmar.
</P>
<P>
He also emphasized the need to go on establishing industries
based on agriculture to boost industrial production.
</P>
<P>
He expects the achievement of sufficiency of edible oil and
less import of it in a few years as national entrepreneurs are
being invited to engage in extending cultivation of seasonal oil
crops and oil-yielding perennial plantations.
</P>
<P>
He urged all the peasants to expand multiple cropping year by
year to improve their socio-economic life and contribute in a way
towards national economic development.
</P>
<P>
He disclosed that the government has been spending substantial
funds and employing various means and making arrangements to
ensure adequate water supply for agricultural purpose in states
and divisions.
</P>
<P>
Myanmar registered a 4.6-percent growth of its gross domestic
product (GDP) in 1997-98 fiscal year, in which agriculture, the
mainstay of the country's economy, grew by 2.9 percent in output
value, accounting for 35.6 percent of the total GDP and about 35
percent of the export. 
</P>
</TEXT>
