<HEADLINE> Kuala Lumpur Stocks Close Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, March 2 (Xinhua) -- Share prices on the Kuala
Lumpur Stock Exchange closed lower Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Trading volume was thin throughout the day as most players are
still adopting a cautious stance while waiting for more
developments in the political and financial scene.
</P>
<P>
At the close, the 100-quality stocks Composite Index shed 5.51
points to 526.03, the all-share Emas Index lost 1.34 points to
133.12, the Industrial Index slipped 2.43 points to 993.38, while
the Second Board Index dropped 1.74 points to 135.70.
</P>
<P>
Losers beat gainers by 428 to 132, with 158 counters unchanged
and 191 untraded.
</P>
<P>
The day's total turnover stood at 84.778 million shares valued
at 179.993 million ringgit (about 47.366 million U.S. dollars)
compared with 77.755 million shares worth 155.991 million ringgit
(about 41.05 million dollars) on Monday. 
</P>
