<HEADLINE> Interview: China's Insurance Enjoys Sound Policy (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 2 (Xinhua) -- The policy China has adopted to
develop its insurance sector is a sound one, which will help
establish a strong local market, said Rolf Hueppi, chairman and
CEO of Zurich Financial Services Group (Zurich).
</P>
<P>
In an interview with Xinhua today, Hueppi said that while
making efforts to standardize the domestic insurance market, the
Chinese financial authorities have been gradually allowing some
overseas companies to enter the marketplace, which is the right
choice for an emerging market.
</P>
<P>
Rolf Hueppi has been visiting China regularly since 1993 when
Zurich set up its representative office in Beijing. He is now in
Beijing meeting with a number of Chinese government officials and
people from the financial sector.
</P>
<P>
He said that the financial services markets around the world
are undergoing dramatic changes as a result of technological and
telecommunications development and economic globalization. He also
commented that the Asian financial crisis has best shown the
volatility of the global financial market.
</P>
<P>
"China has played an important role as a provider of stability
in this region, particularly by not devaluing it's currency, the
yuan," he said, "By opening up the marketplace step by step, China
will have the opportunity to establish itself as a cornerstone of
stability in the financial market."
</P>
<P>
He maintains now that China has developed enough domestic
insurance market practice, knowledge and regulatory competence,
the important thing is to increase the professionalism of the
market. Insurance companies allowed to enter the Chinese market
must be capable of bringing the best global resources and best
practices to this market.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990302.0131 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-03-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Interview: China's Insurance Enjoys Sound Policy (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
He added that the Chinese authorities are doing well by
imposing very strict controls and a regulatory system on the
financial services industry, which is different from the practices
in some crisis-hit Asian countries.
</P>
<P>
He praised that professional level of the people in China's
financial sector, however, he urged that they should be given the
opportunity to be exposed to the best global practices to avoid
making the same mistakes that other emerging markets have made.
</P>
<P>
He said that China's good economic and policy environment has
encouraged companies like Zurich to assist China in building a
professional market environment.
</P>
<P>
Zurich is an international conglomerate with a history of more
than 100 years. It operates property insurance, life insurance, re-
insurance and asset management businesses in over 60 countries,
with total assets of 378 billion U.S. dollars and annual insurance
premiums of 44 billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Presently Zurich is the world's second largest insurance
company and one of the top 10 asset management companies in the
world. 
