<HEADLINE> 20 Multinationals to Attend Beijing High-Tech Industries Week </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 2 (Xinhua) -- Some 20 multinationals will attend
the second Beijing International High-tech Industries Week
scheduled to take place from May 20-24, announced Liu Qi, the
capital's newly-elected mayor.
</P>
<P>
Mayor Liu, who also heads the organizing committee for the
event, pledged at today's press conference that they would turn
the high-tech industries week into a world-level occasion where
customers will be provided with best services regarding the
application of scientific achievements and transaction of
scientific and technological commodities.
</P>
<P>
About 20 countries and regions, including the United States,
Britain, Canada, Germany and Japan have also agreed to send
business delegations.
</P>
<P>
A number of international technology shows, lectures,
technological development fairs, and equipment and technology
purchases for major projects in Beijing will take place during the
event and preparations are nearing completion.
</P>
<P>
The event is jointly sponsored by the Beijing Municipal
Government, the Ministry of Science and Technology and the
Ministry of Foreign Trade and Economic Cooperation.
</P>
<P>
The first such event was held last year and attracted more than
60,000 visitors and resulted in 32 contracts involving a total
investment of 630 million U.S. dollars.  
</P>
