<DOCNO> XIE19990302.0141 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-03-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Malaysia Furniture Export to Increase This Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
According to the Ministry of International Trade and Industry,
Malaysian exports of furniture and related products for last year
totaled 4.362 billion ringgit (about 1.147 billion dollars).
</P>
<P>
"I hope we can achieve an average 40 percent year-on-year
growth in the next six years," Lim told reporters after the
launching ceremony of the Malaysian International Furniture
Exhibition 1999 here Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Lim stressed that the target could be achieved when the local
furniture industry pushed for the upmarket sector where Malaysia
could present furniture of the best quality and design.
</P>
<P>
There are already 3,000 furniture manufacturers in Malaysia, of
which about 300 are regulars exporting their products to almost
121 countries around the world, he said.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition will help to show that our export-oriented
industry has the tremendous potential to meet international
markets, Lim said.
</P>
<P>
In order to help the industry players, he said, the Malaysian
Furniture Design Center will be equipped with facilities to hire
or invite international designers to come and design local
furniture for the international market. 
</P>
