<HEADLINE> China Welcomes Eritrean Acceptance of Agreement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 2 (Xinhua) -- China welcomes the Eritrean
acceptance of a peace initiative put forward by the Organization
of African Unity (OAU) to end its border dispute with neighboring
Ethiopia, foreign ministry Spokesman Zhu Bangzao said on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The acceptance by Eritrea of the Framework Agreement of the
Organization of African Unity will help lead to a peaceful
settlement of the border disputes between the two countries, the
spokesman said at a regular press briefing.
</P>
<P>
Zhu said that China is deeply worried at the rising border
conflicts between Ethiopia and Eritrea which broke out on February
6, and has urged both sides to exercise restraint and immediately
stop the hostilities and confrontation so as to avoid further loss
in human life and property, and create conditions for a peaceful
settlement of the disputes.
</P>
<P>
As a permanent member of the United Nations Security Council,
Zhu said, China is willing to continue its efforts together with
other members of the international community to seek a peaceful
settlement of the border disputes of the two African countries.
</P>
</TEXT>
