<HEADLINE> China Warns Philippines About Nansha Islands Activities </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 2 (Xinhua) -- China is seriously concerned about
the Philippine government's construction of military facilities on
Zhongye Island in the Nansha Islands, according to Chinese Foreign
Ministry Spokesman Zhu Bangzao at a press conference today.
</P>
<P>
 Zhu made the remarks when asked to comment on the recent
statement by a senior Filipino official announcing that the
Philippines intends to expand the airport runway and build
military facilities on Zhongye island in Nansha.
</P>
<P>
 "China has indisputable sovereignty over the Nansha Islands
and its adjacent waters," Zhu said, stressing that Zhongye Island
is part of the Nansha Islands and that the Philippines has
seriously infringed upon China's territory and sovereignty by
illegally intruding onto the island and building military
facilities there.
</P>
<P>
 He went on to say that in recent years the Filipino side has
built numerous military facilities on the islands which it
occupied illegally, sending warships and planes to the Nansha
Islands and conducting military exercises alone or with other
countries in the South China Sea.
</P>
<P>
 "These actions are detrimental to maintaining the peace and
stability in the region and will lead to the further tensions in
the Nansha Islands," Zhu noted.
</P>
<P>
 The Chinese side asked the Filipino side to restrain from
taking any actions that might worsen the situation and create
tensions to maintain stability in the South China Sea area.
</P>
</TEXT>
