UNITED NATIONS -- China, which assumed U.N. Security Council
presidency Monday, will, in strict accordance with the U.N.
Charter, uphold justice and better the efficiency of the 15-member
body when addressing issues concerning international peace and
security within its month-long tenure.
</P>
<P>
