<HEADLINE> OPCW Director General to Visit Pakistan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, March 2 (Xinhua) -- Director General of the
Organization for Prohibition of Chemical Weapons (OPCW) Jose
Mauricio Bustani will arrive here Wednesday for a four-day visit
to Pakistan.
</P>
<P>
This will be the first visit of the director general to
Pakistan after the country became a member of the Chemical Weapons
Convention, according to an official press release issued here
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Pakistan signed the Chemical Weapons Convention on January 14,
1993 and ratified it on October 28, 1997.
</P>
<P>
During his stay here, Bustani will hold meetings with
high-ranking civil and military officials to discuss matters of
mutual interest, said the release.
</P>
<P>
He also plans to visit the country's second biggest city of
Lahore, where he is expected to address the Lahore Chamber of
Commerce, highlighting the implications of the Chemical Weapons
Convention for the chemical industry, the release said.  
</P>
