<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Stock Prices Plunge in Tokyo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, March 2 (Xinhua) -- Japanese stock prices finished lower
Tuesday with the 225-issue Nikkei Stock Average closing below 14,
000 for the first time in more than two weeks.
</P>
<P>
The key index shed 300.69 points, or 2.11 percent, to end at 13,
921.66 as Japanese companies tried to sell their cross-holding
stocks prior to the country's fiscal-year which ends on March 31.
</P>
<P>
Arbitrage-linked selling spurred by a decline in index futures
prices also dampened stock prices, traders said.
</P>
<P>
The broader Tokyo Stock Price Index, covering all first-section
issues, lost 15.73 points or 1.42 percent to 1,092.08 and the
turnover on the major section increased to 457.37 million shares
from Monday's 420.19 million shares.
</P>
<P>
Share prices declined in all business sectors except fishery,
agriculture, electricity and gas.
</P>
<P>
This will not last long "as many investors are waiting to buy
back stocks on dips," said a dealer who believed that the Japanese
government would come out with additional economic stimulus
measures ahead of the local elections scheduled for April.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
