<HEADLINE> EDS-Foreign Loan Management Ministry Calls for Good Management of Foreign Government Loans </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 2 (Xinhua) -- China's Vice-Minister of Finance
Jin Liqun has called for improvement in the management of the
foreign government loans scheme.
</P>
<P>
Jin urged finance departments in all localities to help the
scheme's offices to further improve their work.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out the raising and operation of foreign government
loans are part of the fiscal redistribution work. And the
borrowing, using and repaying of such loans are closely linked up
with government finance, and can affect the international
reputation of a country.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that China's foreign government loans are now under
the direct control of the Ministry of Finance which means there is
proper control of the scale of loans, strict examination and
supervision of loan projects and timely repayments.
</P>
<P>
Between 1979 and September 1998, the governments of 21
countries and two financial institutions had provided loans to
China, with contractual value hitting 42.89 billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
By the end of the period, China had used 36.82 billion dollars
of foreign government loans, and repaid 5.02 billion dollars.
</P>
<P>
There are 1,825 projects funded by foreign government loans, of
which 1,528 have already been completed.  
</P>
</TEXT>
