<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Legislature Active in International Exchanges </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 2 (Xinhua) -- The 9th National People's Congress
(NPC), China's top law-making body, has actively expanded friendly
exchanges with its foreign counterparts since its formation in
March 1998.
</P>
<P>
Through exchanges with its foreign parliaments, the NPC has
publicized the achievements and useful experience of China's
reform and opening-up programs, its NPC system and the development
of its democratic legal system, exchanged views on issues of
common concern with their foreign counterparts, and made clear
Chinese stand on major sovereignty-related issues, according to an
official in charge of the General Office of the NPC Standing
Committee.
</P>
<P>
Said Li Peng, chairman of the 9th NPC Standing Committee: "The
NPC Standing Committee's international exchanges aim to create a
sound international environment for China's reform, opening-up and
modernization drive by promoting world peace and development and a
multi-polarization trend of the world."
</P>
<P>
Since its formation one year ago, the 9th NPC has sent
delegations to a number of foreign countries and international
conferences attended by parliamentary delegations, including the
100th Inter-Parliamentary Conference in Moscow.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, it has received more than 30 foreign congressional
groups and delegations of international congressional associations,
including about 20 speakers and vice-speakers.
</P>
<P>
To facilitate bilateral friendly exchanges, the NPC has
established 51 bilateral friendly groups and associations, and its
special committees have also taken an active part in exchange
activities.
</P>
<P>
Last October, the NPC Standing Committee sponsored the Sixth
General Assembly of the Asia-Pacific Parliamentarians Conference
on Environment and Development (APPCED) in Guilin in China's
Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region.
</P>
<P>
Congressional delegations from 20 countries and observers from
some international organizations attended the meeting. It was an
assembly with most participating countries since the establishment
of APPCED in 1993.
</P>
<P>
Observers hailed the assembly as a great success, saying that
the Guilin Declaration released by the assembly summarizes the
common ground of the participating countries on environment
protection and sustainable development.
</P>
<P>
The NPC also has had direct contacts with leaders and members
of foreign parliaments, helping them understand China better and
enhancing trust and friendship between them and their Chinese
counterparts through visits to China and on-spot observations.
</P>
<P>
The NPC continues to work hard to improve exchanges with
foreign parliamentary organizations. "China's rising status in the
world and its fast-growing economy promise broader prospects for
exchanges between the NPC and foreign parliamentary organizations,
" Li Peng said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
