<HEADLINE> China, U.S to Make Concerted Efforts to Promote Relations: FM </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 2 (Xinhua) -- China and the United States have
agreed that Sino-U.S. relations are very important and both sides
would make concerted efforts to promote bilateral relations,
foreign ministry Spokesman Zhu Bangzao said on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Zhu said at a regular news briefing that during U.S. Secretary
of State Madeleine Albright's visit to China, which concluded on
Tuesday, China and the U.S. agreed to make joint efforts to
promote relations toward the objective of a constructive strategic
partnership for the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
Chinese President Jiang Zemin, Premier Zhu Rongji and Vice-
Premier Qian Qichen all met with Albright on separate occasions,
and had in-depth exchange of views on Sino-U.S. relations and
other international and regional issues of common concern, Zhu
noted.
</P>
<P>
The two sides agreed to step up preparations to make sure that
Premier Zhu Rongji's upcoming visit to the United States in April
will be a success.
</P>
<P>
On the different views on the human rights issue, the spokesman
said that China is willing to work with the United States on the
basis of the three Sino-U.S. joint communique and other joint
statements, and handle the issue properly in the spirit of mutual
respect, treating each other as equals and seeking common ground
while reserving differences. 
</P>
