<HEADLINE> Northeast Chinese Iron, Steel Company Exports More </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, March 2 (Xinhua) -- Benxi Iron and Steel Company (
BISC) in northeast China's Liaoning Province raked in 19.59
million U.S. dollars from export in 1998 despite the adverse
impact of the Asian financial crisis.
</P>
<P>
Information from the company said that it exported 90,900 tons
of iron and steel products in the past year, including 74,800 tons
of pig iron, and 13,200 tons of steel plates.
</P>
<P>
BISC, a major state-owned steelworks with a history of about 90
years, has net fixed assets of 7.25 billion yuan (876 million US
dollars). The company was selected as one of 100 pilot plants to
undertake experiments with the modern enterprise system.
</P>
<P>
The company, which is famous for its high quality products, won
over many new foreign customers in 1998 by striving to improve
services and trying its best to meet clients' demands.
</P>
<P>
The company's clients are distributed in more than 20 countries
and regions. It has became one of China's leading hard currency
earners among the country's iron and steel companies.  
</P>
