<DATE_TIME> 1999-03-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> CPPCC Advice Vital to Decision Making </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 2 (Xinhua) -- Advice on various major state
affairs put forth by members of the Ninth National Committee of
the Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC),
China's top advisory body, has played a vital role in the decision-
making process of the country's top leaders, CPPCC officials said
here today.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that in the past year, various special
committees under the CPPCC National Committee have carried out 65
special investigations into major issues relating to China's
development, and have submitted 57 investigation reports to the
Central Committee of the Communist Party of China (CPC) and the
State Council, China's cabinet.
</P>
<P>
"All these reports and related suggestions have been taken
seriously and highly praised by senior leaders of the central
authorities, and have served as vital references for state policy
making," said a CPPCC official.
</P>
<P>
The Ninth CPPCC National Committee will start its second annual
session Wednesday in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
In 1998, the CPPCC National Committee put forward suggestions
on a wide range of issues, including reform of state-owned
enterprises, guarantee of a basic living standard and re-
employment for workers laid off from state enterprises, anti-
corruption efforts in governments and judicial organs, crackdown
on theft of cultural relics and smuggling, development of the
environmental protection sector and eco-agriculture, and the
promotion of cultural exchanges across the Taiwan Straits.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, officials said that the CPPCC National Committee last
year also organized 179 panel discussions participated by scholars
and experts from various fields to help the central authorities
find solutions to economic and political issues.
</P>
<P>
A report on China's economic situation worked out by the CPPCC
National Committee's Economy Subcommittee became key reference
material during a Central Conference on Economic Work convened at
the end of last year and was highly commended by Premier Zhu
Rongji and Vice-Premier Li Lanqing, they added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
