<HEADLINE> Major Channel of Public Opinions </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 2 (Xinhua) -- The National Committee of the
Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC) and its
committees at various levels have played an important role in
helping the central government and the Chinese Communist Party
Central Committee acquire public opinions and suggestions for
reference in their policy-making.
</P>
<P>
The Ninth CPPCC National Committee received some 3,500 pieces
of information in 1998, the first year of its five-year term, from
its members and non-Communist parties. It also got a total of 18,
567 letters from the people of various social sectors.
</P>
<P>
The information and letters tell the CPPCC problems and topics
of general interest, according to CPPCC sources.
</P>
<P>
The issues and topics include those about how to stop some
people to let farmland go to waste, how to guarantee loans to help
aid the needy, and how to concentrate efforts on resettling people
displaced by the devastating floods, and on preventing diseases
and the springs of river and lake banks.
</P>
<P>
All these have attracted the great attention of the central
leadership, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
CPPCC members at various levels made many fact-finding tours in
grass-roots units across the country to get first-hand information,
which helped address many problems in the life of the people.
</P>
<P>
The CPPCC National Committee has put the findings of its
members and public opinions and suggestions into its either
reports or proposals to the central leadership last year.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
