<DOCNO> XIE19990302.0181 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-03-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Increases Spending in Environmental Protection </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 2 (Xinhua) -- China's redoubled efforts for
environmental protection has resulted in a sharp increase in
investment in this field which came to an equivalent of one
percent of its gross domestic product (GDP) in 1998, according to
the State Environmental Protection Administration.
</P>
<P>
Xie Zhenhua, director of the administration, said in an
exclusive interview with Xinhua that the state approved more than
330 environmental projects in 1998, with a total investment of 107.
6 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
China's annual environmental investment was close to 40 billion
yuan in the period of 1991-1995, only 0.8 percent of the yearly
GDP.
</P>
<P>
Some state financial institutions including the State
Development Bank of China, the Industrial and Commercial Bank of
China and the Construction Bank of China have put a number of
industrial pollution control projects in their major loan support
coverage.
</P>
<P>
"The fund will be mainly used for the control of urban air
pollution and water pollution in majors river and lakes," Xie said.
</P>
<P>
After years of effort, China has scored notable achievement in
water pollution control, with former polluters in the Taihu Lake
and Huaihe River valleys meeting state-set emission standards and
nearly four million cubic meters of silt eliminated in the Dianchi
Lake in southwest China.
</P>
<P>
The state has reduced the production of mines producing high-
sulphur coal and even shut down some of them last year to control
acid rain. As a result, the frequency of acid rain in southwest
China's Chongqing City has declined to 70 percent from the
previous high of 90 percent.
</P>
<P>
China has also decided to ban the use of leaded gasoline
nationwide beginning from January 1, 2000. More than 20 big and
medium-scale cities have already done so. Beijing has even
implemented stricter tail exhaust emission standards to improve
its air quality.
</P>
<P>
"The central government is paying high attention to
environmental protection and the environmental awareness of the
public is improving," Xie said.
</P>
<P>
However, he stressed that with the pollution situation being
serious, much still has to be done in pollution control and
ecological protection.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
