seeded Austrian Thomas Muster 6-4, 7-5 while Frenchman Jerome
Golmard, who picked up his first ATP Tour title last month in
Dubai, beat eighth seed Brazilian Gustavo Kuertan 6-3, 3-6, 6-3.
</P>
<P>
World number one American Pete Sampras, top seed, and last year'
s champion American Andre Agassi, third seed of the tournament,
will play their opening matches on Tuesday night. 
