<HEADLINE> Female Farmers Achieve Prosperity </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 2 (Xinhua) -- The introduction of scientific
farming and animal husbandry techniques has led to a substantial
increase in the number of prosperous female farmers in rural
Beijing.
</P>
<P>
Li Qiaoyun, chairwoman of the Municipal Women's Federation,
made the comment at a Monday conference held to honor the
outstanding achievements of 10 female farmers.
</P>
<P>
She noted that some 170,000 female farmers in the city were
each earning over 10,000 yuan annually by the end of last year,
with income levels for 956 women surpassing 100,000 yuan.
</P>
<P>
Chang Junying, a millionaire honoree from Beijing's Huairou
County, earned her fortune raising rainbow trout. Chang's 1998
income stood at 1.2 million yuan.
</P>
<P>
However, Chang's reputation is based more on the fact that she
donated some 600,000 yuan to poverty-stricken women in her
neighborhood to help them gain affluence.
</P>
<P>
The city women's federation has sponsored 15,000 agricultural
technology courses which have enabled over a million female
farmers to earn certification for various skills.  
</P>
</TEXT>
