<DATE_TIME> 1999-03-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Manila to Draw Up Strategy Against Millennium Bug </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, March 2 (Xinhua) -- The Philippine government would
draw up a national contingency plan in a few months to provide
foolproof safety measures against the millennium bug of computer
systems, government officials said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Officials of the Presidential Commission on Year 2000
Compliance said the commission will require government agencies
this month to submit their contingency plans so it can formulate
the master plan to fortify the country's defense against the
millennium bug.
</P>
<P>
Concerned agencies will carry out the plan then, with the
commission issuing the guidelines on implementation, they said.
</P>
<P>
The National Security Council would be asked to help the
commission implement the plan, which is expected to be drawn up by
September.
</P>
<P>
The millennium bug is a built-in flaw in older computer systems
that uses two digits to mark dates, causing them, for example, to
recognize January 1, 2000 as January 1, 1900.
</P>
<P>
Experts from the world over are holding an international
conference on the problem in Manila to tackle the problem which
may disrupt vital services and transactions across the globe.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
