<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Estrada, Group Leader Talks Postponed for Months </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, March 2 (Xinhua) -- Meeting between Philippine
President Joseph Estrada and Hashim Salamat, chairman of the Moro
Islamic Liberation Front (MILF), was postponed for a few months, a
senior government official said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Roberto Aventajado, president adviser on economic affairs said
the meeting was postponed because of last minute security
arrangements.
</P>
<P>
"We postpone the meeting so we could sort out some security
problems," he said in a radio interview.
</P>
<P>
Asked when the talks could resume, Aventajado said, "perhaps in
the next few months."
</P>
<P>
Aventajado said Salamat already agreed to meet Estrada, who was
visiting Mindanao, the southern Philippines, last Sunday on board
the presidential yacht.
</P>
<P>
Aventajado said what prompted the cancellation of the meeting
was the MILF's concerns about the security en route from the MILF
headquarters to the yacht.
</P>
<P>
Estrada earlier said he was not closing the door on forging
peace with the MILF, despite the cancellation of his scheduled
meeting with Salamat last Sunday.
</P>
<P>
But Estrada has repeatedly said that no talks can be held with
Salamat if it would involve discussing territorial integrity.
</P>
