<HEADLINE> McDyess Named NBA Player of the Week </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, March 1 (Xinhua) -- Denver Nuggets forward Antonio
McDyess, who scored a career-high 46 points last weekend, today
was named NBA Player of the week for the period ending Sunday.
</P>
<P>
McDyess went 16-of-24 from the field and 13-of-17 from the foul
line and also grabbed 19 rebounds Sunday in a 116-112 victory over
the Vancouver Grizzlies.
</P>
<P>
Earlier in the week, McDyess had 22 points and 16 rebounds in
Monday's victory over the Los Angeles Lakers and added 24 points,
four rebounds, four steals and four blocks in a victory over Utah
on Wendesday.
</P>
<P>
For the week, McDyess averaged 24.2 points, 12.2 rebounds, 3.60
blocked shots and 1.60 steals over 38 minutes per game as the
Nuggets won four of five games. He shot 51 percent (45-of-88) from
the field and ranked third in scoring and fourth in blocked shots.
</P>
<P>
Other candidates for the award were Detroit's Joe Dumars and
Grant Hill, Miami's Alonzo Mourning, Philadelphia's Allen Iverson,
Phoenix's Jason Kidd and Seattle's Gary Payton. 
