<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, March 1 (Xinhua) -- Yugoslav President Slobodan
Milosevic said on Monday that the political solution to the Kosovo
issue is to respect Yugoslavia's sovereignty and territorial
integrity and to guarantee the equality of all ethnic nations in
Kosovo.
</P>
<P>
During his meeting with Norwegian Foreign Minister Knut
Vollebaek, the rotating chairman of the Organization for Security
and Cooperation in Europe (OSCE), Milosevic reiterated his belief
that the only way to keep stability and development in Kosovo is
to resolve the conflict peacefully and politically.
</P>
<P>
Yugoslav Foreign Minister Zivorad Jovanovic also discussed with
Vollebaek the mandate of the OSCE observer mission in Kosovo and
the ties between OSCE and Yugoslavia.
</P>
<P>
Jovanovic reaffirmed his opposition to dispatching foreign
troops to Kosovo and urged the OSCE Permanent Council to convene a
special session for cutting aid to Kosovo's Albanian terrorists.
</P>
<P>
Jovanovic also warned that the observer mission should not
exceed its mandate. 
