<DOCNO> XIE19990302.0235 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-03-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Three Measures Recommended to Spur Thai Economy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, March 2 (Xinhua) -- Speeding up spending of the annual
budget, easing conditions for loans for social investment projects
and reducing taxes are the three measures recommended by the prime
minister's advisory team to stimulate the Thai economy, a source
from government house said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
For the annual budget, the advisory team found that the budget
disbursement has been far behind schedule, indicating that there
are problems in state mechanisms.
</P>
<P>
The team has recommended that all ministries be instructed to
prepare a clear spending plan in order to expedite disbursement of
money and each ministry report its spending on a weekly basis if
possible.
</P>
<P>
As for social investment projects, the advisory team said there
are too many conditions for granting loans.
</P>
<P>
It suggested that talks be undertaken with agencies which give
money for the scheme to ease the loan conditions and the operator
of each project, which has obtained the loan, make sure that the
money is spent as soon as possible.
</P>
<P>
Concerning tax reduction, the team proposed that the government
cut tax to increase people's spending power, saying a cut in
value-added tax (VAT) may be the best way of reducing people's
burden.
</P>
<P>
However, the government is reluctant to take this measure since
it is not sure whether a VAT reduction would be able to bring
goods prices down.
</P>
<P>
The government therefore turned the attention to the
possibility of reducing personal income and other taxes, though no
conclusion has been reached. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
