<DATE_TIME> 1999-03-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Motorcycle Market Faces Continuing Fierce Competition </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 2 (Xinhua) -- China's motorcycle output for 1999
will be controlled at a level anywhere between 7-7.5 million units
in order to control rising stockpiles, according to China Goods
and Materials News.
</P>
<P>
While production cuts effectively balanced supply and demand
during 1998, stockpiles remain high and fierce market competition
will continue.
</P>
<P>
Products with high technical contents will be mainly marketed
in cities which currently lack adequate licensing systems for
motorcycle operators.
</P>
<P>
New models will mainly go to inland cities, with relatively
high-grade and some high-grade cycles destined for markets in big
and medium-sized cities and coastal regions.
</P>
<P>
Marketing experts also point to the vast potential for
motorcycle sales in the country's rural areas. 
</P>
</TEXT>
