<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Three Gorges Sites Yield Valuable Relics </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 2 (Xinhua) -- Archaeological excavations at the
Three Gorges Dam Project areas have resulted in rich discoveries,
according to today's China Daily.
</P>
<P>
A group of archaeologists from the Institute of Vertebrate
Palaeontology and Palaeoanthropology under the Chinese Academy of
Sciences, Beijing University, Jilin University and Chongqing
Museum launched their excavations in the dam area last October.
</P>
<P>
Bronze weapons have been found at the Lijiaba site in Yunyang
County, a Shang Dynasty site (circa 1600-1100 BC) to the Han
Dynasty (206 BC-AD 220), and archaeologists say they are very
important discoveries concerning the ancient Ba and Shu cultures.
</P>
<P>
A specialist from the State Bureau of Cultural Relics said that
the Lijiaba site will be indispensable for future study of the Ba
and Shu cultures.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, excavations at the Zhongba site in Zhongxian
County have unearthed remains that belong to the Neolithic Period.
</P>
<P>
In the Suolong site in Wushan County, archaeologists determined
that the excavated pottery, stone and boneware were important
remains of the Longshan Culture, which also belonged to the
Neolithic Period.
</P>
<P>
The Chongqing Museum group has also found a valuable ancient
tomb of the Six Dynasties (AD 220-589).  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990302.0248 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-03-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Brazil to Lease Airbase for Foreign Space Launchings </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Rio de Janeiro, March 1 (Xinhua) -- Brazil's aeronautic
authorities announced Monday that they will lease the Alcantar
airbase for space launchings to foreign firms.
</P>
<P>
The Alcantar base, which is located in the state of Maranhao,
in the northeast section of the country, is of primary interest to
other nations because of its geographical location, which is close
to the equator and provides ease of entry into space for
positioning orbiting satellites.
</P>
<P>
Certain major industries engaged in the exploration of space
transport, travel and communications, such as the North American
firms of Boeing, Lockheed-Martin and Orbital Science Corporation,
the French company Matra Marconi, and the Italian company Fiat
Avio, have expressed their interest in the base.
</P>
<P>
A spokesperson for The Brazilian firm, Infra-Estructurae
Aeroportuaria (Infraera), signed a contract with the Fiat Avio
company. The Italian company intends to have a definite agreement
about future rocket launchings by the end of the year.
</P>
<P>
The head of the Department of Aerospatial Development of
Infraero, Joao Ribeiro, Jr., said the government would invest 50
million U.S. dollars to improve the airfield's infrastructure.
</P>
</TEXT>
