<HEADLINE> EDS-Farmers-Fake Products China to Check Quality of Crop Seeds, Fertilizers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 2 (Xinhua) -- China will soon launch a
nationwide check on crop seeds, farm chemicals and fertilizers, in
the wake of rampant fakes and shoddy products.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry of Agriculture "has received consistent reports
that fake and shoddy products have harmed farmers," said Vice-
Minister Liu Jian, quoted by the China Daily today.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that no crop seeds, pesticides or fertilizers
should be allowed to enter the market without prior checks and
registration.
</P>
<P>
In the first half of 1998, at least 40,000 tons of fertilizers,
14,000 tons of pesticides and 2,500 tons of seeds were found to be
fake or inferior in quality, according to sources with the State
Administration of Industry and Commerce.
</P>
<P>
China produced about 490 million tons of grain last year and
the output for this year is expected to remain the same level.
</P>
</TEXT>
