<BODY>
<HEADLINE> EDS-College Entrance China Seeks Public Ideas for College Entrance Exam </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 2 (Xinhua) -- Chinese now have a chance to
contribute to the national college examination after the Ministry
of Education issued a call for more ideas from society.
</P>
<P>
The ministry will begin collecting examination questions from
all over the country on a list of comprehensive subjects.
</P>
<P>
The ministry has made a draft of an exam subjects, content, and
form, with content as the emphasis for reforming the college
entrance examination system.
</P>
<P>
Ma Jinke, director of the ministry's test center, said that the
changes will focus on practical ability and qualities, and the
design will follow a middle school teaching outline and include
new elements that help colleges select good students and encourage
middle schools to improve their quality.
</P>
<P>
The ministry will spend three years implementing a "3+X" exam
plan, the "3" being compulsory subjects like Chinese, mathematics
and foreign languages, and the "X" being electives from physics,
chemistry, biology, politics, history, or geography, or subjects
that test students' practical abilities.
</P>
<P>
The test design committee will choose questions from outside
the university. The ministry has a web site for the purpose at:
http://www.neea.edu.cn/zhnl.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
