<BODY>
<HEADLINE> American Judicial Officials Meeting in Peru </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Lima, March 1 (Xinhua)-- American judicial officials gathered
in Lima Monday to attend a two-day meeting on justice issues.
</P>
<P>
Peruvian President Alberto Fujimori opened the meeting by
saying "it is not question of doing away with the State of
Legality, but rather of adapting it so as to improve the justice
of American countries."
</P>
<P>
To achieve a complete judicial reform, it needs to incorporate
new concepts of justice within a new democratic culture and with
the application of mechanisms for a reform of judicial power, he
added.
</P>
<P>
Justice ministers and attorney generals from 24 member
countries of the Organization of American States (OAS) and OAS's
General Secretary Cesar Gaviria attended the opening ceremony.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
