<DOCNO> XIE19990302.0273 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-03-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Backgrounder: Major Events of Tibet (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
-- On May 23, 1951, the Agreement of the Central People's
Government and the Local Government of Tibet on Measures for the
Peaceful Liberation of Tibet (i.e., the 17-Article Agreement) was
signed after the delegates of the central people's government and
the Tibetan local government had reached agreement on a series of
questions concerning Tibet's peaceful liberation.
</P>
<P>
-- On October 26, 1951, with the support of the Tibetan people,
the People's Liberation Army entered Lhasa.
</P>
<P>
-- On April 22, 1956, the Dalai Lama became chairman of the
Preparatory Committee for the Tibet Autonomous Region.
</P>
<P>
-- On March 10, 1959, some Tibetan serf-owners and foreign anti-
China forces launched an armed rebellion in Lhasa, and the People'
s Liberation Army put down the rebellious activities in downtown
Lhasa on March 22.
</P>
<P>
-- The Central People's Government implemented the democratic
reform that focused on the abolition of serfdom in Tibet after
putting down the rebellion in 1959.
</P>
<P>
-- The Tibet Autonomous Region was formally founded in 1965,
with Ngapoi Ngawang Jigme as the first chairman of the Region.
</P>
<P>
-- On May 30, 1972, Premier Zhou Enlai approved the
construction of an oil pipeline from Gelmud in northwest China's
Qinghai province to Lhasa which was completed in 1976.
</P>
<P>
-- The first geothermal power station of Tibet was built up and
put into use on January 21, 1978.
</P>
<P>
-- Between February 27-28, 1984, the Secretariat of the Central
Committee of the Communist Party of China held the second work
conference on Tibet. The CPC Central Committee and the State
Council decided that nine provinces and municipalities including
Beijing offer 43 assistance projects to Tibet.
</P>
<P>
-- On December 28, 1989, the 10th Panchen Lama passed away in
Xigaze, Tibet, at the age of 51.
</P>
<P>
-- The central government held the third work conference on
Tibet in 1994 and decided to offer 62 projects to assist Tibet
economic construction.
</P>
<P>
-- The State Council approved Gyaincain Norbu as the 11th
Panchen Lama in November 1995. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990302.0274 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-03-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Indonesia Expects 1999 Rice Production to Rise </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, March 2 (Xinhua) -- Indonesia's Central Bureau of
Statistics (BPS) and the Agriculture Ministry predicted that rice
production in 1999 may increase by 0.39 percent from 48.47 million
tons in 1998 to 48.66 million tons.
</P>
<P>
Compared to the 1997 production of 49.38 million tons, last
year's output declined 1.83 percent, Antara News Agency Tuesday
quoted BPS spokesman Bambang Kristianto as saying.
</P>
<P>
In 1999, soybean production may be 1.30 million tons, a decline
of 0.75 percent compared to the 1.31 million tons in 1998, while
1.36 million tons had been produced in 1997.
</P>
<P>
The production of corn is estimated also to decline by 13.68
percent from 10.66 million tons to 8.77 million tons, mungbean
from 300,000 tons to 260,000 tons, and peanut from 690,000 tons to
660,000 tons.
</P>
<P>
The production of sweet potato is expected to drop from 1.95
million tons to 1.87 million tons, while that of cassava from
14.73 million tons to 14.74 million tons. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990302.0275 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-03-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> EDS-Catering Service China's Catering Industry Continues to Prosper </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 2 (Xinhua) -- China's catering services reported
a total turnover of 278.3 billion yuan for 1998, an annual growth
of 15.7 percent, according to the latest figures from the National
Bureau of Statistics.
</P>
<P>
The State Administration of Internal Trade said it expects this
momentum to continue.
</P>
<P>
According to its projections, the catering industry will
achieve a growth rate of around 15 percent this year, and annual
revenues will exceed 300 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
In an analysis report, the administration said a trend of more
frugal spending was evident last year, as luxurious consumption,
engaged in mostly by institutions, decreased while individual and
family spending increased.
</P>
<P>
Restaurants now are offering more flexible services to meet the
new needs of their customers. More and more people are now
availing themselves of take-out and delivery services, and more
ready-to-cook dishes are available in grocery stores.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
