<BODY>
<HEADLINE> EDS-Construction Supervision China Doing Nationwide Check on Construction Sector </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 2 (Xinhua) -- China has begun a nationwide check
on its construction industry, which is designed to improve project
quality and create conditions for fairer competition.
</P>
<P>
The campaign will focus on malpractice in design, construction,
and personnel in housing and infrastructure projects each costing
500,000 yuan (about 60,000 U.S. dollars) or more.
</P>
<P>
It is also intended to ensure that bids, supervisory work, and
quality controls on all projects are followed in accordance with
rules and regulations and will look for improper distribution of
bids, random reduction of the construction time, and illegal bids.
</P>
<P>
Market analysts say that the campaign comes on the heels of a
series of construction problems in recent months.  
</P>
</TEXT>
