<HEADLINE> Iverson Named Player of Month </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, March 1 (Xinhua) -- Allen Iverson, who has led
Philadelphia to its best start in eight seasons, on Monday was
named NBA Player of the Month.
</P>
<P>
Iverson became the delayed season's first Player of the Month
by averaging an NBA-leading 28.5 points with 6.0 assists, 5.8
rebounds and 2.31 steals in February for the 76ers, who are 8-5
and tied for third in the Atlantic Division.
</P>
<P>
The small, speedy guard exploded for a season-high 46 points
against San Antonio on February 12, which tied Detroit's Grant
Hill and Antonio McDyess of the Denver Nuggets for the highest-
scoring game this season.
</P>
<P>
Iverson became the first 76er to win the award since Charles
Barkley in November 1988. Wilt Chamberlain in 1965-66 was the last
76er to lead the league in scoring. 
</P>
</TEXT>
