<BODY>
<HEADLINE> FIFA Delegation Begins Final Inspection on Youth Cup Facilities </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, March 1 (Xinhua) -- A FIFA delegation has begun final
checks in Nigeria on facilities for the world youth cup next month.
</P>
<P>
"The Jack Warner-led team is only carrying out last-minute
checks to ensure we've followed their instructions on the
facilities," said Emiko Bake, spokesman for the Nigerian
organisers of the tournament.
</P>
<P>
Although it said it was satisfied with facilities after an
inspection visit last month, the FIFA team criticised hotels and
stadiums in some of the eight venues, saying they had not met the
necessary standards.
</P>
<P>
"Their findings won't affect Nigeria's status of hosting the
tournament," Bake said. "But we've been working hard to ensure all
the facilities meet the required standards."
</P>
<P>
The draw is in the capital Abuja on Friday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
