<HEADLINE> Vogts Joins Moenchengladbach as Director </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, March 1 (Xinhua) -- Former Germany coach Berti Vogts has
become the director of his old club Borussia Moenchengladbach, the
Bundesliga's bottom club, local reports said here on Monday.
</P>
<P>
"I am convinced that better times are coming," said Vogts who
helped Moenchengladbach to five German titles and two UEFA Cup
triumphs in the 1970s.
</P>
<P>
Vogts, who quit as coach of the national side last September,
said his job would be an administrative one.
</P>
<P>
Rainer Bonhof, Vogts's former team mate and his assistant with
the national side, is the current Moenchengladbach coach. 
