<HEADLINE> Chelsea Tipped for Premiership Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, March 1 (Xinhua) -- Chelsea are the current favourites
to take the Premiership title, according to Arsenal boss, local
report quoted Arsenal Arsene Wenger as saying on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The Frenchman, who watched his side drop two points in Sunday's
1-1 draw at Newcastle, said that United's involvement in the
Champions League may just give the Londoner's the edge.
</P>
<P>
"I would give a slight advantage to Chelsea," Wenger said.
</P>
<P>
"Not because of a difference in quality of teams, but
Manchester United are much more involved in the European Cup,
while Chelsea play in the Cup-winners' Cup with less demands.
</P>
<P>
Speaking in The Mail newspaper, Wenger said: "The Champions'
Cup is something special in everybody's mind - and I would say
even more so in United's mind - so I think they might lose more
energy."
</P>
<P>
Arsenal, with 11 matches left to play, now have 50 points,
three behind Chelsea and seven adrift of leaders United, who have
played one game more.
</P>
<P>
But Wenger warns that Arsenal cannot be ruled out either.
</P>
<P>
"Everybody will drop points, but now, because of this result,
we can afford fewer mistakes than the others," he said.
</P>
<P>
"There is still a long way to go, though, and Manchester United
have to come to Newcastle shortly. They won't find it easy," he
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
