<HEADLINE> Stocks End Mixed on Wall Street </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, March 1 (Xinhua) -- Wall Street stocks ended mixed
Monday with the Dow Jones industrial average moving in the
positive territory after plunging last week.
</P>
<P>
The Dow closed at 9,324.78, up 18.20 from a morning loss of
83.40 points. The index suffered a total loss of 246.09 points in
the previous four sessions of trading.
</P>
<P>
The technology heavy Nasdaq composite index was up 7.15 at
2,295.18. The index lost 38.79 points last Friday.
</P>
<P>
A rise in Americans' personal income in January had an effect
on the stock market. The Commerce Department reported that the
personal income increased 0.6 percent in January, pushing the
index of purchasing activity up to 52.4 percent in February from
49.5 percent in the previous month.
</P>
<P>
The surging both in personal income and purchasing activity
kept investors in worries that the economy is growing fast enough
to spark inflation, which, they think, could prompt the Federal
Reserve to raise interest rates.
</P>
<P>
The Standard &AMP; Poor's 500 index was down 2.17 at 1,236.16 and
the NYSE index was down 1.03 at 585.43.
</P>
<P>
The American Stock Exchange index was unchanged at 698.29 while
the Russell 2000 index of smaller companies rose 2.13 to 394.39.
</P>
</TEXT>
