<HEADLINE> German Machinery, Steel Industries Drops </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, March 1 (Xinhua) -- In a further sign of trouble for the
German economy, the machinery and steel-industry sectors showed
double-digit declines in the month of January, according to
reports published Monday.
</P>
<P>
The machinery producers association VDMA said new orders in
January were down by 16 percent from the same month last year.
</P>
<P>
It said the decline included a 19 percent plunge in foreign
orders, while domestic orders were off by 12 percent.
</P>
<P>
And the steel sector branch of the Federal Statistics Office
also said steel production in January came to 3.09 million tons,
down 21.4 percent compared with the same month last year.
</P>
<P>
The office said pig iron output was down by 25.76 percent to
2.09 million tons, while warm-rolled steel production fell 22
percent to 2.55 million tons. 
</P>
